Star.Name: 21Alp And
Star.LongName: ALPHERATZ; Alpherat; Sirrah; Sirah. Also formerly called Delta Peg.

Star.Name: 51 And
Star.LongName: 51 And also called Upsilon Per, but outside IAU boundaries of Perseus.

Star.Name: 22Bet Aqr
Star.LongName: Sadalsuud; Sadalsud; Sad es Saud; Sadalsund; Saad el Sund.

Star.Name: 34Alp Aqr
Star.LongName: SADALMELIK; Sadalmelek; Sadlamulk; El Melik; Saad el Melik.

Star.Name: 71Tau2Aqr
Star.LongName: Sometimes called Tau2 Aqr; usually without superscript.

Star.Name: 69Tau1Aqr
Star.LongName: Sometimes called Tau1 Aqr; usually no Greek letter. See HR 8679.

Star.Name: 17Zet Aql
Star.LongName: Deneb el Okab; Deneb. Combined with HR 7176.

Star.Name: 13Eps Aql
Star.LongName: Deneb el Okab; Deneb. Names combined with HR 7235.

Star.Name: 13Alp Ari
Star.LongName: HAMAL; Hemal; Hamul; Ras Hammel; El Nath (obsolete). The name Arietis also used both for the star and the constellation.

Star.Name: 5Gam1Ari
Star.LongName: The HD numbers and other data, especially spectral classes, for HR 545-6 have frequently been interchanged. HD 11502 is the brighter = HR 546, while HD 11503 = HR 545 is the slightly fainter N. prec. component B of ADS 1507.

Star.Name: 45Rho2Ari
Star.LongName: Rho1 Fl 44, Rho2 Fl 45, Rho3 Fl 46 Ari are, respectively, HD 18091 (6.93v, A3), HR 867 and 869. HR 869 is also called simply Rho Ari.

Star.Name: 10Eta Aur
Star.LongName: Hoedus II. One of the kids, with HR 1612.

Star.Name: 8Zet Aur
Star.LongName: Haedi; Haedus; Hoedus I. With HR 1641, one of the "kids"; Sadatoni; Saclateni.

Star.Name: 30Xi Aur
Star.LongName: Flamsteed also called this star 32 Cam = 30 Aur.

Star.Name: 60 Aur
Star.LongName: Sometimes this star, sometimes HR 2547 have been called Psi8 Aur. To avoid future confusion this designation is abandoned for both.

Star.Name: 36Eps Boo
Star.LongName: IZAR; Mirac; Mirak; Mirach; Mizar, a name commonly applied to HR 5054; Pulcherrima.

Star.Name: 38 Boo
Star.LongName: Merga; Marrha; El Mara el Musalsela; Falx Italica.

Star.Name: 15 Cnc
Star.LongName: 15 Cnc is also Psi Gem, in Cancer.

Star.Name: 14Psi Cnc
Star.LongName: Psi2 Fl 14 Cnc. Psi1 Fl 13 is HD 67690 (6.7v, K0). HR 3191 also called simply Psi Cnc.

Star.Name: 46 Cnc
Star.LongName: BAC and Heis (Argelander) differ on the correspondence between Flamsteed numbers and Bayer letters. The Heis convention is adopted here. The corresponding interpretations are as follows: HR, FL, Heis, BAC; 3464, 46, -, Sigma1; 3519, 51, Sigma1, -; 3532, 57, -, Sigma2; 3555, 59, Sigma2, -; 3563, 61, -, Sigma3; 3575, 64, Sigma3, -. In the Bayer atlas (1603) the letter Sigma is in a position between these two groups (BAC being south of Heis configurations) and could apply just as well to either. Most older catalogues give the BAC convention.

Star.Name: 53 Cnc
Star.LongName: BAC and others call this Rho1, HR 3522 Rho2, and HR 3540 Rho3.

Star.Name: 24 Cnc
Star.LongName: BAC and some old catalogues call 24 CNC = Upsilon1; HR 3329 = 28 = Upsilon2; HR 3355 = 30 = Upsilon3. Most modern catalogues follow Heis identifications: HR 3355 = 30 = Upsilon1; HR 3369 = 32 = Upsilon2.

Star.Name: 8Bet CVn
Star.LongName: Chara is the name assigned either to this star or, more generally, to the "southern hound" of the constellation Canes Venatici; the northern "hound" is called Asterion, a name not generally assigned any particular star.

Star.Name: 15 CMa
Star.LongName: Old sources call this Pi1 CMa, HR 2558 Pi2 and HR 2590 Pi3. Superscripts no longer retained.

Star.Name: 49Del Cap
Star.LongName: Deneb Algedi; Deneb Algiedi; Scheddi; Sheddi.

Star.Name: 9Bet Cap
Star.LongName: Dabih. Beta1 = Dabih Major; Beta2 = Dabih Minor.

Star.Name: 6Alp2Cap
Star.LongName: Secunda Giedi; Algiedi Secunda; Gredi; Algedi, with HR 7747.

Star.Name: 34Zet Cap
Star.LongName: DM is CoD (star moved from -23d zone to -22d zone between 1855 and 1875). In Southern Durchmusterung extension (Schoenfeld 1886), SD-23d442.

Star.Name: 5Alp1Cap
Star.LongName: Prima Giedi; Algiedi Prima; Algedi with HR 7754.

Star.Name: 14Tau Cap
Star.LongName: Tau1 Fl 13 and Tau2 Fl 14 Cap are, respectively, HD 196348 (6.76V, K3III) and HR 7889, the former being in the BS Supplement. HR 7889 is usually called simply Tau Cap.

Star.Name: 11Bet Cas
Star.LongName: Caph; Chaph; Kaff; Al Sanam al Nakah.

Star.Name: 37Del Cas
Star.LongName: Ruchbah; Rucba; Rucha; also Ksora in Becvar.

Star.Name: 45Eps Cas
Star.LongName: Called Segin in Becvar; Allen gives Ruchbah, a name more commonly applied to HR 403.

Star.Name: 24Eta Cas
Star.LongName: Achird, according to Becvar; Allen says "unnamed".

Star.Name: Mu Cep
Star.LongName: Herschel's "Garnet Star". Both Bayer (1603) and Argelander (1843) showed Mu Cep in the position of 14 Cep = HR 8406. Heis (1872), however, in cataloguing the stars in Argelander's Atlas, misidentified Mu as the star currently known as the variable Mu Cep (HR 8316). A third star, 13 Cep (HR 8371), was identified in BAC and numerous subsequent old catalogues as Mu Cep. See HR 8371, HR 8406.

Star.Name: 14 Cep
Star.LongName: Identifed as Mu Cep in "Uranometria Nova". This is as consistent with the Bayer Mu as HR 8316, but nearly all other sources abide by the identification of Mu Cep as HR 8316. See HR 8316, HR 8371.

Star.Name: 13 Cep
Star.LongName: Identified in BAC and other old catalogues as Mu Cep, but this is inconsistant with Bayer's Mu. See HR 8316, HR 8406.

Star.Name: 16Bet Cet
Star.LongName: DIPHDA; Deneb Kaitos; Difda; Difda al Thani; Rana Secunda, the "Second Frog" (the "First Frog" is Fomalhaut = HR 8728).

Star.Name: 8Iot Cet
Star.LongName: Deneb Kaitos Shemali; Deneb Kaitos Al Shamaliyy.

Star.Name: 91Lam Cet
Star.LongName: Menkar, a name usually used for HR 911.

Star.Name: 5Alp CrB
Star.LongName: ALPHEKKA; Alphecca; Alphacca; Gemma; Gnosia; The Jewel; Gnosia Stella Coronae; Ashtaroth.

Star.Name: 4Gam Crv
Star.LongName: Gienah Ghurab; Gienah, a name also applied to HR 7949.

Star.Name: 9Bet Crv
Star.LongName: Kraz in Becvar; Allen says unnamed.

Star.Name: 1Alp Crv
Star.LongName: Alchiba; Alchita; Al Minliar al Ghurab; Al Chiba.

Star.Name: 50Alp Cyg
Star.LongName: DENEB; Deneb Cygni; Deneb el Adige; Arided; Aridif; Gallina; Arrioph.

Star.Name: 53Eps Cyg
Star.LongName: Gienah Cygni; Gienah, also applied to HR 4662.

Star.Name: 32 Cyg
Star.LongName: Originally called Omicron2 Cyg in GCVS, the name has been changed to V1488 Cyg because of much confusion as to which star is Omicron1, which Omicron2. See HR 7730.

Star.Name: 30 Cyg
Star.LongName: There is very much confusion in the literature as to which of the three stars HR 7730, 7735, 7751 should be called Omicron1 and which Omricron2: HR FL SOME BAC Others 7730 30 Omicron1 Omicron1 - 7735 31 Omicron2 Omicron2 Omicron1 7751 32 - Omicron3 Omicron2 For these stars, the Greek letter is hence omitted from the Name column.

Star.Name: 45Ome1Cyg
Star.LongName: See HR 7828. In the older literature HR 7844 often confused with HR 7851 (q.v.) because the magnitudes and separations of the two brighter components of each, 7844AB, 7851AC, are nearly the same, although the position angles differ. In Allen under the star named Ruchba the P.A. corresponds to HR 7844 while the color clearly refers to HR 7851.

Star.Name: 46Ome2Cyg
Star.LongName: See HR 7828, 7844. Ruchba; Rukbat al-dajajah; Al Rukbah al Dajajah.

Star.Name: 43 Cyg
Star.LongName: Omega Cyg, a case similar to Omicron Cyg (HR 7730): HR, FL, PGC-BAC, Heis-HR; 7828, 43, Omega1, -; 7844, 45, Omega2, Omega1; 7851, 46, Omega3, Omega2.

Star.Name: 33Gam Dra
Star.LongName: ETAMIN; Etanin; Ettanin; Rastaban; Rasaben; Zenith Star.

Star.Name: 57Del Dra
Star.LongName: Nodus Secundus; Altais; Aldib, a name corresponding to a group rather than to a single star.

Star.Name: 12Iot Dra
Star.LongName: Ed Asich; Eldsich; Al Dhiba; Al Dhihi.

Star.Name: 11Alp Dra
Star.LongName: THUBAN; Adib; Dragon's Tail. Former Pole Star, about 2700 B.C.

Star.Name: 31Psi1Dra
Star.LongName: Some catalogues call HR 6636 Psi1, 6637 Psi2; most, however, call 6636/7 Psi1 and 6725 Psi2.

Star.Name: 21Mu Dra
Star.LongName: Arrakis; Errakis; Al Rakis; El Rakis.

Star.Name: 3 Equ
Star.LongName: Some early sources called this Zeta Equ. Not retained. Not Zeta in Bayer.

Star.Name: 23Del Eri
Star.LongName: Rana in Becvar. But see HR 188.

Star.Name: 52Ups2Eri
Star.LongName: Theemim; Beemin. Allen applies this name, after Bayer, to the series of stars, Upsilon1 through Upsilon7 Eri, or HR 1143, 1195, 1214, 1347, 1393, 1453 and 1464. (The order of the superscripts varies among different catalogues.)

Star.Name: 2Tau2Eri
Star.LongName: Angetenar; Al Anchat al Nahr; Anchat.

Star.Name: 13Zet Eri
Star.LongName: Zibal in Becvar, but this does not correspond to the position of Al Zibal (in Phoenix) described by Allen.

Star.Name: 15 Eri
Star.LongName: CoD-22d1146 = CPD-22d 349; south of -23d at epoch 1855, but in Southern Durchmusterung extension as SD-23d 44.

Star.Name: 60Iot Gem
Star.LongName: Propus, a name more commonly applied to HR 2216.

Star.Name: 1 Gem
Star.LongName: Propus, a name more commonly applied to HR 2216.

Star.Name: Tau1Gru
Star.LongName: Tau1, Tau2 and Tau3 Gru are, respectively, HR 8700, HD 216655/6 (7.03V, G3/6 and 6.67V, F5V) and HR 8722. HD 216655/6 are in BS Supplement.

Star.Name: 76Lam Her
Star.LongName: Maasym; Masym; Misam, a name also applied to h and Chi Per.

Star.Name: 30Alp Hya
Star.LongName: ALPHARD; Alfard; Alphart; Kalbelaphard; Cor Hydrae.

Star.Name: Phi3Hya
Star.LongName: Phi in most catalogues. Becvar calls it Phi1 but Delalande- Baily call it Phi3; their Phi1 is a 7.12 mag. star 4 min. prec., HD 91369.

Star.Name: 33 Hya
Star.LongName: Heis-Argelander call this A Hya whereas BAC calls 28 Hya = HR 3738A. Bayer letter A marked so that any or all HR 3738, 3750, 3814 could have been designated as A.

Star.Name: 28 Hya
Star.LongName: In many older catalogues called A Hya; in Bayer, 3 stars are near the letter A, of which the brightest is 33 Hya = HR 3814, another HR 3750.

Star.Name: Phi2Hya
Star.LongName: Phi1, Phi2 and Phi3 Hya are, respectively, HD 91369 (7.64v, G5), HR 4156 and 4171. HR 4171 also called simply Phi Hya.

Star.Name: Eta2Hyi
Star.LongName: Eta2 Hyi. Eta1 is the fainter Bayer component, HD 11733, 6.8v, A0.

Star.Name: 32Alp Leo
Star.LongName: REGULUS; Cor Leonis; Rex; Al Kalb al Asad; Kabeleced.

Star.Name: 68Del Leo
Star.LongName: Zosma; Zozma; Zosca; Zozca; Duhr; Dhur; Zubra.

Star.Name: 17Eps Leo
Star.LongName: Ras Elased Australis; Al Ras al Asad al Janubiyyah; Algenubi; with HR 3905, Al Ashfar.

Star.Name: 24Mu Leo
Star.LongName: Ras Elased Borealis; Rasalas; Ras al Asad al Shamaliyy; Alshemali; with HR 3873, Al Ashfar.

Star.Name: 1 Lep
Star.LongName: DM is CoD number (star moved from -23d zone to -22d zone between 1855 and 1875); in Southern Durchmusterung extension as SD-23d 65.

Star.Name: 27Bet Lib
Star.LongName: Zuben Elschemali; Zuben Eschamali; Zuben el Chamali; Zubenesch; Zubenelg; Kiffa Borealis.

Star.Name: 9Alp2Lib
Star.LongName: Zuben Elgenubi; Zubenelgenubi; Kiffa Australis; Elkhiffa Australis.

Star.Name: 20Sig Lib
Star.LongName: Brachium; Cornu; Zuben el Genubi; Zuban al Akrab; Zuben Hakrabi. Sigma Lib is also Gamma Sco, in Lib.

Star.Name: 38Gam Lib
Star.LongName: Zuben Elakrab; Zuben Hakraki; Zuben el Hakrabi.

Star.Name: 32Zet1Lib
Star.LongName: Zeta1 Fl 32, Zeta2 Fl 34, Zeta3 Fl 34 and Zeta4 Fl 35 Lib are, respectively, HR 5743, HD 137949 (6.69V, F0Vp), HR 5750 and 5764. HD 137949 is included in the BS Supplement. HR 5764 also called simply Zeta Lib.

Star.Name: 4Eps1Lyr
Star.LongName: With HR 7052-4 called the Double Double in Lyra.

Star.Name: 26Alp Mon
Star.LongName: In early catalogues called Gamma Mon; HR 2227 now called Gamma, was Alpha in BAC and numerous older catalogues.

Star.Name: 5Gam Mon
Star.LongName: Called Alpha Mon in BAC and many early catalogues. Now HR 2970 is called Alpha Mon.

Star.Name: Sig Oct
Star.LongName: Polaris Australis (so called by Wollaston in 1789).

Star.Name: 60Bet Oph
Star.LongName: Cebalrai; Kelb Alrai; Kabalrai; Cheleb; Celb-al-Rai.

Star.Name: 58Alp Ori
Star.LongName: BETELGEUSE; Betelguex; Betelgeuze; Beteiguex; Al Mankib.

Star.Name: 44Iot Ori
Star.LongName: Nair al Saif; Hatysa in Becvar.

Star.Name: 1Pi 3Ori
Star.LongName: Designated Tabit by Becvar but Allen gives Thabit as Burritt's name for an unlettered star on his atlas, the Upsilon of Heis (HR 1855). The superscripts for Pi Ori adopted in the Harvard catalogues and taken over in the BS correspond to the Heis atlas and Argelander's identifications of Flamsteed numbers. Very many old catalogues follow the BAC. Heis superscripts 1,2,3,4 are respectively 4,2,1,3 in the BAC.

Star.Name: 8Eps Peg
Star.LongName: ENIF; Enf; Enir; Al Anf; Os Pegasi; Fom.

Star.Name: 26Bet Per
Star.LongName: ALGOL; Gorgona; Gorgonea Prima; Demon Star; El Ghoul.

Star.Name: 15Eta Per
Star.LongName: Miram in Becvar; Allen says unnamed.

Star.Name: Alp Phe
Star.LongName: ANKAA; Nair al Zaurak; Cymbae; Lucida Cymbae; Head of Phoenix.

Star.Name: 113Alp Psc
Star.LongName: Alrisha; Alrischa; Alrescha; El Rischa; Al Richa; Rescha; Okda; Kaitain.

Star.Name: 24Alp PsA
Star.LongName: FOMALHAUT; Os Piscis Meridiani; Os Piscis Notii; Difda al Auwel, the "First Frog."

Star.Name: 15Rho Pup
Star.LongName: Called Iota Pup in Argelander's atlas, and in Bayer.

Star.Name: 7Xi Pup
Star.LongName: Azmidiske; Asmidiske, a name more properly applied to HR 3699 according to Allen.

Star.Name: 3 Pup
Star.LongName: Called Tau in Argelander, Bayer, HP 1462, (but now Tau is HR 2553). HR 2996 called l in HR 50 and Lacaille 1763.

Star.Name: 5Alp Sge
Star.LongName: Sham; Alsahm. Names originally corresponded to whole constellation Sagitta.

Star.Name: 1 Sge
Star.LongName: 1 Sge on borderline of Vul. Listed as Vul in BAC.

Star.Name: 10Gam2Sgr
Star.LongName: Nash; Alnasl; Alwazl; Zujj al Nushshabah; Nushaba. Gamma1 or gamma2 Sgr; see HR 6742.

Star.Name: Alp Sgr
Star.LongName: Rukbat; Rucba; Rukbat al Rami; Alrami.

Star.Name: Bet1Sgr
Star.LongName: Arkab Prior; Arkab or Urkab with HR 7343.

Star.Name: Bet2Sgr
Star.LongName: Arkab Posterior; Arkab or Urkab with HR 7337.

Star.Name: Gam1Sgr
Star.LongName: Although HR 6742 and 6746 are named gamma1 and gamma2 Sgr, respectively, more often 6746 is simply called gamma Sgr and the Greek letter is omitted for HR 6742.

Star.Name: 47Chi1Sgr
Star.LongName: Chi1 Fl 47, Chi2 Fl 48 and Chi3 Fl 49 Sgr are, respectively, HR 7362, HD 182391 (7.08v, B9) and HR 7363.

Star.Name: 21Alp Sco
Star.LongName: ANTARES; Cor Scorpii; Kalb al Akrab; Vespertilio.

Star.Name: 8Bet1Sco
Star.LongName: Graffias; Grafias; Grassias; Acrab; Akrab; Elacrab.

Star.Name: 20Sig Sco
Star.LongName: Alniyat; Al Niyat. Name applies to pair with HR 6165.

Star.Name: Xi Sco
Star.LongName: Has been called Grafias, a name more commonly applied to HR 5984.

Star.Name: 15Psi Sco
Star.LongName: Some early catalogues (particlarly BAC) call Flamsteed 15 Chi instead of Psi Sco and leave 17 (HR 6048 = Chi) unnumbered. All later sources adopt the convention followed here.

Star.Name: 24Alp Ser
Star.LongName: UNUKALHAI; Unuk al Hay; Unuk Elhaia; Unuk; Unukalhay; Cor Serpentis.

Star.Name: 61 Ser
Star.LongName: Some older catalogues following BAC call this e Ser. However, Heis and followers, including HR, call HR 6993 = e.

Star.Name: 112Bet Tau
Star.LongName: ALNATH; EL NATH; Nath. Beta Tau is also Gamma Aur, in Taurus.

Star.Name: 25Eta Tau
Star.LongName: ALCYONE. The brightest of the Pleiades.

Star.Name: 69Ups Tau
Star.LongName: Some sources call this Upsilon1 and HR 1399 Upsilon2 Tau; other catalogues reverse these designations. The superscripts now rarely used and Upsilon retained for 69 Tau.

Star.Name: 2Alp Tri
Star.LongName: Metallah; Mothallah; Atria; Caput Trianguli; Ras al Muthallah; Elmuthalleth.

Star.Name: 64Gam UMa
Star.LongName: PHAD; Phecda; Phekda; Phegda; Phekha; Phacd.

Star.Name: 1Omi UMa
Star.LongName: Muscida; a name also applied to Pi UMa, HR 3391, 3403.

Star.Name: 33Lam UMa
Star.LongName: Tania Borealis. With HR 4069, Al Kafzah al Thaniyah.

Star.Name: 63Chi UMa
Star.LongName: Discordances as to whether Xi or Iota and Kappa UMa (HR 3569, 3594) should be El Koprah, Alkaphrah.

Star.Name: 1Alp UMi
Star.LongName: POLARIS; Alruccabah; Cynosura; Phoenice; Lodestar; Pole Star; Tramontana; Angel Stern; Navigatoria; Star of Arcady; Yilduz; Mismar.

Star.Name: 7Bet UMi
Star.LongName: KOCAB; Kochab; Kochah; with HR 5735 called "Guards of the Pole."

Star.Name: 13Gam UMi
Star.LongName: Pherkad; Pherkad Major. See HR 5563 and 5714.

Star.Name: 11 UMi
Star.LongName: Pherkad Minor. Sometimes called Gamma1 UMi. HR 5735 is Gamma or Gamma2.

Star.Name: Gam2Vel
Star.LongName: Suhail al Muhlif; Al Suhail al Muhlif; "Spectral Gem of Southern Skies".

Star.Name: Lam Vel
Star.LongName: Alsuhail; Al Suhail al Wazn; Suhail.

Star.Name: 67Alp Vir
Star.LongName: SPICA; Azimech; Spica Virginis; Alaraph, a name also given HR 4540, 4932.

Star.Name: 47Eps Vir
Star.LongName: VINDEMIATRIX; Vindemiator; Vendemiatrix; Almuredin; Provindemiator; Protrigetrix; Protrygetor; Alaraph, a name also applied to HR 4540 and 5056.

Star.Name: 43Del Vir
Star.LongName: Auva; Minelauva in Becvar, a name Smyth assigned Beta Vir = HR 4540.

Star.Name: 5Bet Vir
Star.LongName: Zavijah; Zavijava; Zavyava; Zawijah; Zarijan; Minelauva; Alaraph, a name also applied to HR 4932 and 5056.
